                <note rend="inline" type="source">702.2211/57: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">De Lambert</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-07-28T14:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 28, 1925—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>25. Your 33, July 21, 11 a.m.<note n="11" xml:id="d53fn11">Not printed; the
                        Chargé reported among other matters that the regime in Ecuador had requested
                        him to ascertain if the United States would grant exequaturs to new
                        Ecuadoran consular officers (file No. 822.00/596).</note> While Department
                    can not issue exequaturs to consular officers holding commissions from an
                    unrecognized regime it would be disposed at the request of the Ecuadoran
                    Legation to permit Consular officers appointed by the authorities now
                    functioning in Ecuador to carry on their duties provisionally without
                        exequaturs.<note n="12" xml:id="d53fn12">Subsequently the regime in Ecuador
                        appointed Señor de Ycaza to be consul general at New York, and he was
                        permitted to carry on his duties (file No. 702.2211/59).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
